At First, Open your Bit Integrations Dashboard and create an integrations by clicking the “Create Integrations” button. Now select the eForm that you want to integrate with ActiveCampaign. Select the form name from the Drop-Down list that you want to integrate with ActiveCampaign, . And click on the “Next” button. And select ActiveCampaign. Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken “ActiveCampaign”. Access API URL & API key: To get the URL & key : log in to ActiveCampaign dashboard=> Settings=> Developer=> Get your API URL & Key.You have to copy the API URL & Key from the Active Campaign Developer section & paste the URL & key on the fields of integration settings. Now click Authorize, & you are ready to integrate with your ActiveCampaign account. After successful authorization. Select the List from the drop-down option. You have to create a list before on your ActiveCampaign account. You can add a Tag [ also multiple tags] for the Contacts that you have created before on your ActiveCampaign account You will find the Map Field option. You have to map all the necessary form fields with the related ActiveCampaign field. Here ‘Email‘ field is the default for ActiveCampaign.

You can also update the submitted data by enabling the action called Update ActiveCampaign. Suppose the user already submitted data under an email address. Again they want to submit data under the same email, if the action is enabled, then the new data will be updated regarding that email address. Now save the integration by clicking the "Finish & Save." Button {" "} We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

At First, Open your Bit Integrations Dashboard and create an integrations by clicking the “Create Integrations” button. Now select eForm that you want to integrate with Mailchimp. Select the form name from the Drop-Down list that you want to integrate with Mailchimp. And click on the “Next” button. And select Mailchimp. Integration Name: Set the proper integration name. Default it's taken “Mailchimp”. Client ID & Client Secret: To get new Client Id & Client secret go to Mailchimp API CONSOLE > Register An App. In the App website & Redirect URL fields you have to give the values of the field of Homepage URL & Authorized Redirect URL respectively. Now, click on the “Create” button. You have to copy the Client ID & Client secret from MailChimp & paste the Client ID & Client secret on the fields of integration settings. And click on the "Authorize" button. Select the audience from the drop-down option. You have to create an audience before on your Mailchimp account. You can add a Tag [ also multiple tags] for the audience that you have created before on your MailChimp account. When you fill-up the audience list field, you will find the Map Field option. You have to map all the necessary form fields with the related Mailchimp field.

Also, you can enable the action Add Address Field to add the address of the contact. The addresses fields of Mailchimp are fixed – Address, City, Zip & State. These fields are required for the Mailchimp audience. By enabling the action Double-Opt-in admin can ask permission from users if they want to subscribe to MailChimp or not. You can also update the submitted data by enabling the action called Update Mailchimp. Suppose the user already submitted data under an email address. Again they want to submit data under the same email, if the action is enabled then the new data will be updated regarding that email address.
After clicking on Finish & Save, the Mailchimp integration is ready. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

At First, Open your Bit Integrations Dashboard and create an integrations by clicking the “Create Integrations” button. Now select eForm that you want to integrate with Zoho Campaign. Select the form name from the Drop-Down list that you want to integrate with Zoho Campaign. And click on the “Next” button. And select Zoho Campaign. Integration Name: Set the proper integration name Default it's taken “Zoho Campaigns”. Select a data center from the dropdown. Then click on the Zoho API Console. Navigate to API Console-> Get Started-> Server-based Applications. Fill those fields (Homepage URL and Authorized Redirect URLs) the same as your Integration Homepage. Then click CREATE button A Client ID and a Client Secret will be generated. Then go to the Client Secret tab Then copy the Client ID and Client Secret and paste it to the Bit Integrations integration page. Then click on the Authorize button (wait for a few seconds). After the successful authorization click on the Next button Select the contact List and the mandatory field from the dropdown. When you fill-up the contact list field, you will find the Map Field option. You have to map all the necessary form fields with the related Zoho Campaigns field.

After clicking on Finish & Save, the Zoho Campaign integration is ready. Notice: When you send data in Zoho Campaign an email confirmation message will go to the typed email. The data will not insert before the confirmation. If you want to send data without email confirmation, you have to change some settings in the Zoho Campaign. Have to disable SIGNUP FORM. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

At First, Open your Bit Integrations Dashboard and create an integrations by clicking the “Create Integrations” button. Now select eForm that you want to integrate with Zoho Bigin. Select the form name from the Drop-Down list that you want to integrate with Zoho Bigin. And click on the “Next” button. And select Zoho Bigin. Integration Name: Set the proper integration name Default it's taken “Zoho Bigin”. Select a data center from the dropdown. Then click on the Zoho API Console. Navigate to API Console-> Get Started-> Server-based Applications. Fill those fields (Homepage URL and Authorized Redirect URLs) the same as your Integration Homepage. Then click CREATE button A Client ID and a Client Secret will be generated. Then go to the Client Secret tab Then copy the Client ID and Client Secret and paste it to the Bit Form integration page. Then click on the Authorize button (wait for a few seconds). After the successful authorization click on the Next button Select a Module from the drop-down list. Map all the mandatory Recruit fields to the corresponding fields in your form.

Workflow: Select this option to trigger the Zoho Bigin workflow for the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho Bigin workflow for the selected module doesn’t work. Attachment: To Select this option you can send file upload field data to Zoho Bigin related list Attachments. You can also send file upload field data to Zoho Bigin via normal field mapping). Please select the CRM file upload field from the drop-down which you want to send data. Approval: Select this option to automatically send form data to your Zoho Bigin approval list instead of adding them. Add Note: Select this action to add a note from eForm to Zoho Bigin account automatically. Upload Photo: You can update any contact’s profile photo through our Bit Form to your Zoho Bigin account. For that, hoover on the action called “Upload Photo“. After mapping the relevant fields, click the action ‘Upload Photo’ to upload a photo from Bit Form to Zoho Bigin. Now click on ‘Save’. Whenever the user fills-up the form on Bit Form, the image will be automatically uploaded as a profile photo to the Zoho Bigin account.

After giving all the required information, click on Finish & Save. Now your created Zoho Bigin API is ready for implementation. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

At First, Open your Bit Integrations Dashboard and create an integrations by clicking the “Create Integrations” button. Now select eForm that you want to integrate with Telegram. Select the form name from the Drop-Down list that you want to integrate with Telegram. And click on the “Next” button. And select Telegram. Integration Name: Set the proper integration name Default it's taken “Telegram”. To get the API Key, visit your telegram account. Now, search for @BotFather. If you have created a bot before, then just copy the API key & past the key on the API Key field on the eForm integration page else, create a new one by sending a command /newbot to @BotFather Authorize the entire settings. Click on Next for further integration settings ahead. Click on the drop-down & select the specific chat list you have created earlier on Telegram. A. Sometimes you may not find the lists of your telegram account. One thing you can do that – go to your telegram account, then remove the administrator’s bot from that specific list or group & add again the administrator’s bot. B. To remove the bot & re-add the bot follow the path: Click on your desired list/group/Channel => Go to settings of that list/group/Channel => Administrator => Remove the promoted bot & add again the administrator’s bot Select the parse_mode method to send text notifications to the specified group or channel. You can use either HTML or Markdown format to send a message. Now, type a message as your preference. You can select Form Fields to fetch the user information if you want. Also, you can mention any group or channels from this message field.

You can select the action Attachment right below the Message’ field. Enabling this action, you can send – Audio, Video, Photo, or Document from eForm to Telegram. After this, click on the Next option.
To successfully integrate your form with Telegram click the Finish & Save button. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

At First, Open your Bit Integrations Dashboard and create an integrations by clicking the “Create Integrations” button. Now select eForm that you want to integrate with Zoho CRM. Select the form name from the Drop-Down list that you want to integrate with Zoho CRM. And click on the “Next” button. And select Zoho CRM. Integration Name: Set the proper integration name Default it's taken “Zoho CRM”. Select a data center from the dropdown. Then click on the Zoho API Console. Navigate to API Console-> Get Started-> Server-based Applications. Fill those fields (Homepage URL and Authorized Redirect URLs) the same as your Integration Homepage. Then click CREATE button A Client ID and a Client Secret will be generated. Then go to the Client Secret tab Then copy the Client ID and Client Secret and paste it to the Bit Integrations integration page. Then click on the Authorize button (wait for a few seconds). After the successful authorization click on the Next button Select a Module and Layout from the drop-down list. Map all the mandatory CRM fields to the corresponding fields in your form.
You can send data Zoho CRM related list from eForm. Select the required related list module and layout from the drop-down provided. Then map the mandatory field. To map more fields, click on the (+).

Map all the fields, select the necessary Actions to be performed on integration, and then click on the Save button to save your settings. All the actions are described below. Workflow: Select this option to trigger the Zoho CRM workflow to relevant the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho CRM workflow to relevant the selected module doesn’t work. Attachment: To Select this option you can send file upload field data to Zoho CRM related list Attachments. You can also send file upload field data to Zoho CRM via normal field mapping). Please select the CRM file upload field from the drop-down which you want to send data. Approval: Select this option to automatically send form data to your Zoho CRM approval list instead of adding them. Blueprint: Select this option to trigger the Zoho CRM blueprint to relevant the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho CRM blueprint to relevant the selected module doesn’t work. Upsert Record: Upon selecting the option YES, if a record with the identical value exists in Zoho CRM, it will be updated with the new values. If you select NO, a new record will be created in Zoho CRM. You can arrange fields in the order in which upsert should happen. The record will update based on email address. Assignment Rules: When you choose this option, Assignment Rules defined in Zoho CRM can be triggered when form entries are added to a CRM module. Please select the assignment rule from the drop-down which you want to trigger. Tag Records: When you choose this option, you can add a tag to the records that are pushed to Zoho CRM. It helps you to search for records in CRM by tag. There has a list of tag records in the dropdown. You can use Zoho CRM by default tag, form fields also can add a custom tag. Record Owner: Select this option you can set a record owner of the sent record.
After clicking on Finish & Save, the Zoho CRM integration is ready. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

Then click CREATE button A Client ID and a Client Secret will be generated. Then go to the Client Secret tab Then copy the Client ID and Client Secret and paste it to the Bit Integrations integration page. Then click on the Authorize button (wait for a few seconds). After the successful authorization click on the Next button Select a Module and Layout from the drop-down list. Map all the mandatory CRM fields to the corresponding fields in your form.

You can send data Zoho CRM related list from Fluent Forms. Select the required related list module and layout from the drop-down provided. Then map the mandatory field. To map more fields, click on the (+).

Workflow: Select this option to trigger the Zoho CRM workflow to relevant the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho CRM workflow to relevant the selected module doesn’t work. Attachment: To Select this option you can send file upload field data to Zoho CRM related list Attachments. You can also send file upload field data to Zoho CRM via normal field mapping). Please select the CRM file upload field from the drop-down which you want to send data. Approval: Select this option to automatically send form data to your Zoho CRM approval list instead of adding them. Blueprint: Select this option to trigger the Zoho CRM blueprint to relevant the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho CRM blueprint to relevant the selected module doesn’t work. Blueprint: Select this option to trigger the Zoho CRM blueprint to relevant the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho CRM blueprint to relevant the selected module doesn’t work. Upsert Record: Upon selecting the option YES, if a record with the identical value exists in Zoho CRM, it will be updated with the new values. If you select NO, a new record will be created in Zoho CRM. You can arrange fields in the order in which upsert should happen. The record will update based on email address. Assignment Rules: When you choose this option, Assignment Rules defined in Zoho CRM can be triggered when form entries are added to a CRM module. Please select the assignment rule from the drop-down which you want to trigger. Tag Records: When you choose this option, you can add a tag to the records that are pushed to Zoho CRM. It helps you to search for records in CRM by tag. There has a list of tag records in the dropdown. You can use Zoho CRM by default tag, form fields also can add a custom tag. Record Owner: Select this option you can set a record owner of the sent record.
After clicking on Finish & Save, the Zoho CRM integration is ready. We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.

Responses of the report manage submission data properly. Information gathered using a form needs to be presented for viewing. Once the form is successfully submitted, data will be added as a new row into the responses of the database when you hit the button of the form. We can easily manage, delete, update, filter, clone, and duplicate records. The features are shown below: ✔ View:/Detail View ✔ Column Reorder ✔ Adjustable Column Width ✔ Delete, Edit and duplicate ✔ Column Visibility ✔ Export Data

You can also view a maximum of 100 records on a single page. You can go next and previous pages by a single click. To the bottom right corner of the response page there is a option for showing a specific number of records on each page. Moreover, you can also sort record. If you click on any specific record you will see the record details as popup details views to the left.

You can easily reorder column by just dragging and dropping the mouse over the column title. If you have a column name First Name on the first column and Last Name on the second column. Now you can alter their position. If you hover the mouse over the column title, an option will be available to reorder respective column positions’ back and forth.
You can easily adjust column width by dragging your mouse onto it.

You can delete, edit, update or duplicate a specific record. You can also delete, duplicate and edit Bulk records.If you go to the very left of every specific record and click on three dots. You will find there the options will be available for delete, edit or duplicate. Suppose, you have two records with the same email = “test@test.com” so you can click on the record and delete the desired one. If you have 2000 records in your response and you want to delete them. For this you can select the multiple records together and click on the delete button to delete them together. This way you can delete all records from responses in a few attempts. You do not need to go through every record and delete them one by one.

You can easily hide and show columns in a single click of mouse. Suppose, you have many fields in your form and you want to show a few fields of them like First Name ➤ Last Name ➤ Phone ➤ Message. On the left side of responses you see an Eye icon. Just click on it and you will see all the fields will be available. You can put check mark only the fields you want to show and others keep unchecked.

You can export all the responses management data by clicking Export Data. When you click on Export data, a new window will be displayed where you will find 5 fields. These fields allow you to choose rows you want to export from Bit Form. Follow the below instructions: ➤ Click on export data from Form Responses & a window will be shown. ➤ How many rows to export: There you will find two options from the drop-down menu. Options are : All & Choose input number. You can export all rows or you can input row numbers as you want. If you select Choose input number then another field Enter your row number will arrive. ➤ Sort By: You can sort data in ascending or descending order. ➤ Select the sort field: You have to choose the fields that you want to sort. ➤ Export file format: You can choose 9 types of form to which you will export all data. Formats are : CSV, Xlsx, Xls, Fods, Ods, Prn, Text, HTML & Eth. ➤ Export all fields: If you want to export all the fields of the row then click on Yes or you can specify the fields you need to export by clicking No.

documents.s: WS Form Integration With Zoho Recruit

documents.t: At First, Open your Bit Integrations Dashboard and create an integrations by clicking the “Create Integrations” button. Now select WS Form that you want to integrate with Zoho Recruit. Select the form name from the Drop-Down list that you want to integrate with Zoho Recruit. And click on the “Next” button. And select Zoho Recruit. Integration Name: Set the proper integration name Default it's taken “Zoho Recruit”. Select a data center from the dropdown. Then click on the Zoho API Console. Navigate to API Console-> Get Started-> Server-based Applications. Fill those fields (Homepage URL and Authorized Redirect URLs) the same as your Integration Homepage. Then click CREATE button A Client ID and a Client Secret will be generated. Then go to the Client Secret tab Then copy the Client ID and Client Secret and paste it to the Bit Integrations integration page. Then click on the Authorize button (wait for a few seconds). After the successful authorization click on the Next button Select a Module from the drop-down list. Map all the mandatory Recruit fields to the corresponding fields in your form. If you use File Upload field should to map this separately.

You can send data to Zoho Recruit related list from WS Form. Select the required related list module and layout from the drop-down provided. Then map the mandatory field. To map more fields, click on the (+).

Workflow: Select this option to trigger the Zoho Recruit workflow for the selected module. If you didn’t select this option Zoho Recruit workflow for the selected module doesn’t work. Approval: Select this option to automatically send form data to your Zoho Recruit approval list instead of adding them. Upsert Record: : When you choose the Upsert Record option, if a record with the identical value exists in Zoho Recruit, then it will be updated with the new values. If not, a new record will be created. Add Note: Select this action to add a note from WS Form to Zoho Recruit account automatically. Record Owner: YSelect this option you can set a record owner of the sent record. For this, you have to copy the Owner ID from Zoho Recruit and paste it here.

After giving all the required information, click on Finish & Save. Now your created Zoho Recruit API is ready for implementation We have an option in every integration "Timeline," where you can check integration success or error status.
